knowledge_graph.title: Sugar substitute
knowledge_graph.description: A sugar substitute is a food additive that provides a sweetness like that of sugar while containing significantly less food energy than sugar-based sweeteners, making it a zero-calorie or low-calorie sweetener.

related_questions.snippet: You can opt for coconut sugar, honey, maple syrup, and agave nectar, which are some good and healthy options.
